<h2>11 landing page trends to watch for and try in 2023</h2>
<p>Now, there are lots of landing page trends we‚Äôre expecting to see this year‚ÄîAI generated design, immersive 3D animations, ChatGPT in action. But not every trend with the newest technology will work for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">your audience</a> (or, let‚Äôs be honest, your budget). So here are the 11 landing page trends that are straightforward to implement so you can get started with right away.</p>
<h3>1. Exceptional product videos</h3>
<p>This list isn‚Äôt ranked, but this is the first clear trend for a reason: Your product videos should be a high-priority <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/04/marketing-collateral">marketing asset</a>. One that you use again and again. It‚Äôs no wonder we‚Äôre seeing these front-and-center on more and more landing pages.</p>
<p>Your product videos should already be sleek and enough to anchor these pages. The key to using them effectively is selecting the most relevant or appealing portions and splicing away. Goldcast, an event marketing software, does this really well.</p>
